  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the thyme and cook for another minute, until slightly wilted.",
    "Place the sea bass fillets in the skillet, skin side up (if they have skin).",
    "Season with salt, black pepper, and smoked paprika.",
    "Squeeze the lemon and orange juice over the fish.",
    "Add the cherry tomatoes to the skillet and toss to combine.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and bake for 8-10 minutes, until the fish is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.",
    "Remove from the oven and serve immediately."
  ],
